    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 4.0",
    "body" : "<p>Given your comment <a href=\"https://stackoverflow.com/questions/58913450/comparing-two-columns-in-hibernate-criteria?noredirect=1#comment104089122_58913450\">here</a>, you'll have to do a full table scan, which will create troubles with a bigger table. You will likely need to change your approach altogether, and introduce a field which says something like \"IsUpdated\". Or, when creating that record, <code>UpdatedTime</code> should be set to null, indicating it hasn't been updated yet. Then, you can do a query like \"give all records where UpdatedTime is not null\".</p>\n"
